name: Phantom Year One: In The Eye Of The Hurricane

description:
Offered exclusively through Typhoo Tea as a mail-order promotional item, The Amazing World of Doctor Who reprinted several comic strips and prose stories from the 1976 Doctor Who Annual, along with a couple of new prose tales, The Vampires of Crellium and On the Slippery Trail. Typhoo, whose name comes from the Chinese word for Doctor, is a well known brand of tea in Britain. Both of the new stories in this rare book were later reprinted in World Distributors' 1981 Doctor Who: Adventures in Time and Space, and again in 1984's Doctor Who Special - Journey Through Time.

Contents

Prose stories

  1. The Sinister Sponge
  2. The Vampires of Crellium
  3. On the Slippery Trail
  4. The Mission

Comic strips

  1. The Psychic Jungle
  2. A Fresh Start
  3. Neuronic Nightmare

A Fresh Start was originally titled Eve of the War when it was printed in the 1976 Annual. Despite appearing on the cover, the Daleks, Cybermen, Sea Devils and Zygons do not appear in any of the stories inside.
